About us

The House of Representatives is convened for the first time not later than 20 days after the election results are published. The Speaker of the previous convocation convenes the first session and chairs the session pending the election of the new Speaker of the House of Representatives.

If the Speaker of the previous convocation is not in a position to convene the session of the House of Representatives, the session is convened by the eldest member within the new composition of the House of Representatives.
